<TITLE> Laxman celebrates anniversary with century </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KOLKATA, India, Feb 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Vangipurappu Laxman celebrated his sixth wedding anniversary with a century that put India in control of the second and final Test against South Africa on Tuesday. Laxman carved out an unbeaten 143 and put on 259 in an Indian record seventh wicket stand with skipper Mahendra Singh Dhoni (132 not out) to help India declare at 643-6, a lead of 347 on the third day. "Today is my marriage anniversary and it is great that my wife and kids gave me a surprise by coming to Kolkata," Laxman told reporters after scoring his 15th Test hundred. "So, definitely I would like to dedicate this to my wife because she has been a pillar of strength to me and my family. "It is tough being the wife of a cricketer because we are always on the r
